# .cursorrules — v3.2
# Copy this file verbatim into the root of every new project as .cursorrules.
# Cursor reads this automatically at the start of every session.
# This is the condensed, always-present context layer.
# The full rules live in FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md and PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md in the repo root.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# THE STACK
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
This project uses:
- Vite + React + TypeScript (strict mode) + Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config via @theme in src/index.css; NO tailwind.config.ts)
- @tailwindcss/vite plugin (no PostCSS config needed)
- tw-animate-css for animation utilities (replaces tailwindcss-animate)
- shadcn/ui (new-york style) for component primitives (in src/components/ui/ — do not edit)
- lucide-react for icons — NO OTHER icon libraries
- react-router-dom v6 (pinned to ^6 — v7 imports change but our patterns work)
- usePageMeta hook for SEO metadata (NO react-helmet-async — direct document.title + meta updates)
- Supabase for auth and database (migrations under supabase/migrations/, not SQL Editor)
- Stripe for payments (added in Phase 7B) — monthly + annual prices, raw body on webhooks
- Resend for email (added in Phase 7C)
- Anthropic for AI features — check docs.anthropic.com/models for current recommended model
  (baseline when this project started: claude-sonnet-4-6; always verify, model names drift)
- Upstash Redis for rate limiting (added in Phase 7A) — TWO layers: IP-keyed + user-keyed
- Sentry v10 for error tracking (added in Phase 7D) — uses createRoot error handlers (React 19+)
- PostHog for product analytics (only after cookie consent; session replay masks all inputs)
- Vercel for hosting — API routes live at /api/*.ts at REPO ROOT (NOT src/api/)
- TanStack Query for server-state data (Supabase queries/mutations); React useState for UI-only state
- Node 22 LTS (active until April 2027)
- ESLint v9 flat config (eslint.config.js — NO .eslintrc.* files)

Built locally from day one. No Lovable, no code-generation fork step — the
project was scaffolded in Cursor and all commits come from here.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PROJECT STRUCTURE (non-negotiable — from PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Configuration is split across THREE files:
- src/config/site.ts      → brand identity, nav, per-route meta tags, social
- src/config/content.ts   → all visible page copy (hero, features, testimonials, etc.)
- src/config/pricing.ts   → plans, prices, Stripe price IDs
- src/config/env.ts       → env var validation (throws clear errors at startup)
Pick the right config file for each piece of copy. Do NOT recombine into one file.

Design tokens:
- src/index.css          → @theme block — atomic tokens (colours, fonts, radius)
- src/components/ui/variants.ts → component tokens (CVA configs for buttons/cards/badges/inputs/nav-tabs/links)

Pages: flat `src/pages/` (no public/auth/app subdirectories).

Components:
- src/components/ui/          shadcn primitives — do not edit; barrel-exported via index.ts
- src/components/layout/      Navbar, Footer, PageContainer, Section, AuthGuard, PageMeta, ScrollToTop, LegalPageLayout
- src/components/sections/    HeroSection, FeaturesSection, PricingSection, etc.
- src/components/cards/       FeatureCard, PricingCard, TestimonialCard
- src/components/forms/       LoginForm, SignupForm, ForgotPasswordForm, ContactForm, FeedbackForm
- src/components/shared/      Skeleton, ErrorState, EmptyState, LoadingSpinner, Logo, CookieConsent

API routes → /api/*.ts at REPO ROOT (Vercel serverless convention).
FORBIDDEN: creating API files under src/api/ — they won't deploy as Vercel functions, they'll bundle as dead code.

Types → src/types/ (database.ts generated by supabase gen types)
Hooks → src/hooks/
Lib utilities → src/lib/ (supabase.ts, stripe.ts, email.ts, logger.ts, ratelimit.ts, analytics.ts, utils.ts)
Migrations → supabase/migrations/ (run via `supabase db push`, never the SQL Editor)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# THE THIRTEEN RULES THAT NEVER BEND
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## 1. Content
Never hardcode visible UI text in components. Always import from the right config file:
- Brand/nav/meta → site from src/config/site.ts
- Section copy → content from src/config/content.ts
- Pricing → pricingConfig from src/config/pricing.ts
If you find yourself typing a string literal inside a .tsx file, stop.
Add it to the appropriate config first.

## 2a. Atomic design tokens (Tailwind v4)
Never use arbitrary Tailwind values.
FORBIDDEN: p-[13px], text-[17px], text-[#3c3c3c], shadow-[0_2px_5px_rgba(0,0,0,0.08)], z-[999], w-[500px].
Use token classes generated from src/index.css @theme block. If a needed value doesn't exist, add it to @theme as a CSS variable (e.g. `--color-brand-300: oklch(...)` in @theme makes `bg-brand-300`, `text-brand-300` available automatically).
Never hardcode hex colours anywhere.
Never import arbitrary CSS. Use Tailwind classes or CSS variables only.
Tailwind v4 has NO `tailwind.config.ts`. If you start writing one, stop.

## 2b. Component tokens (variants.ts)
Never style a button, card, badge, or input inline — use the variants from src/components/ui/variants.ts.

FORBIDDEN:
  <button className="bg-brand-500 hover:bg-brand-600 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-white font-semibold">
CORRECT:
  <Button variant="primary" size="md">      (uses buttonVariants from variants.ts)
  OR: <button className={buttonVariants({ variant: 'primary', size: 'md' })}>

Why this matters: atomic tokens keep individual values consistent. Component tokens keep the SHAPE of repeated UI elements consistent. Two buttons can both use tokens (rounded-lg vs rounded-md, p-4 vs p-5) and still drift. variants.ts prevents that drift.

When a section needs a component shape that doesn't exist yet (e.g. a "tertiary" button variant, or a "compact" card), ADD IT TO variants.ts FIRST, then use it. Never inline a one-off.

This applies to: button, card, badge, nav tab, input, pricing emphasis, link.

## 3. Interactive states (FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md Section 10)
Every button, link, and input MUST have all five states:
- default    (base classes)
- hover:     (mouse over)
- focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 (keyboard focus)
- active:    (pressed — e.g. active:scale-[0.98] or active:bg-brand-700)
- disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:pointer-events-none

Use `focus-visible`, not `focus`. `focus-visible` shows ring only for keyboard users.
Removing `focus:outline-none` without replacing with a visible ring is a BLOCKING error.

## 4. Typography
- All font sizes via Tailwind text-* utilities (rem). Never px for type.
- Body text minimum text-base (16px) — especially inputs on mobile (iOS Safari auto-zooms below 16px).
- No more than 5 type sizes on a single page.
- Headings never skip levels (no h2 → h4). One <h1> per page.
- Use text-balance on headings, text-pretty on body paragraphs.
- max-w-prose on every body text paragraph.

## 5. Responsive
- Mobile-first. Write 375px styles first, then md: and lg: prefixes.
- Test mentally at 375 / 768 / 1280.
- Use 100dvh, not 100vh (iOS address bar causes overflow with 100vh).
- Touch targets ≥ 44px on mobile for standalone interactive elements.
- Navigation transforms to hamburger at md: breakpoint.

## 6. Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA — legal requirement)
- Semantic HTML first. ARIA only when native semantics can't express meaning.
- Body contrast ≥ 4.5:1. Large text / UI contrast ≥ 3:1.
- Every <img>: width, height, alt (empty string if decorative), loading attribute.
- Every <input>: visible <label> with matching for/id, correct type, autoComplete. Placeholder is NEVER a substitute for label.
- Every icon-only button: aria-label.
- One <h1> per page. Logical heading hierarchy.
- Skip-to-content link as first element after <body>.
- role="alert" on error messages. aria-live on dynamic content.
- Honour prefers-reduced-motion in globals.css.
- Focus ring always visible on every interactive element.

## 7. Database and security
- Every new Supabase table gets RLS ENABLED the moment it is created.
- Every RLS policy reviewed — no "using (true)" on tables with user data.
- Every API route accepting user input: authentication → rate limiting → input validation (in that order).
- Never put API keys in code. They live in .env locally and Vercel env vars in production.
- Never commit .env. Always check .env is in .gitignore.

## 8. Error handling
- Iron Law: NO FIX WITHOUT ROOT CAUSE FIRST. Explain what is broken and why, then propose the fix.
- No console.log in production code. Use src/lib/logger.ts.
- Catch all errors in API routes. Sentry.captureException. Return safe messages — never expose raw errors to users.
- TypeScript strict. Never use `any` — use explicit types or `unknown`.

## 9. Stripe
- Webhook handler always verifies Stripe signature before processing.
- Webhook receives RAW body, not parsed JSON. Body parser disabled for /api/webhook.
- Any webhook event handler that writes to DB checks the stripe_events idempotency table first.
- Never trust client-submitted pricing — always look up via STRIPE_PRICE_ID env var.

## 10. Email
- All sending goes through src/lib/email.ts — never call Resend directly from a component or API route.
- Always use EMAIL_FROM env var. Never hardcode an email address.
- Never send from noreply@ — use hello@ or team@.

## 11. Vercel function timeouts
- API routes that call external APIs (Anthropic, Stripe) MUST have maxDuration set in vercel.json.
- Default 10s will timeout many AI responses.
- Baseline: 60s for /api/generate, 30s for all other outbound-call routes, 15s for feedback, 5s for health.
- On Hobby plan: max 60s per function. On Pro: max 300s.

## 12. Server state vs UI state
- Server data (anything fetched from Supabase or APIs): TanStack Query (useQuery, useMutation).
  Never use useEffect + useState for data fetching — causes race conditions, stale data, no retries.
- UI-only state (modals, toggles, form input before submit): React useState. No library.
- Global client-only state (user session, theme): React Context or Zustand, but only if prop drilling
  reaches 3+ levels. Do not add Redux.

## 13. Privacy and session replay
- Any component rendering AI output, user-submitted content, or sensitive text: add className="sensitive"
  so PostHog session replay masks it (configured in analytics.ts).
- Never log userInput, AI responses, passwords, tokens, emails, payment data, or anything identifying.
- console.log is forbidden in api/* — use src/lib/logger.ts which respects env and structured format.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CONVENTIONAL COMMITS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Every commit message follows the pattern:
  (feat|fix|chore|docs|style|refactor|test|perf|ci)(scope)?: description

Examples:
  feat(hero): add animated gradient background
  fix(auth): redirect preserves returnTo query param
  chore: bump @supabase/supabase-js to 2.39.0
  docs(claude): update known issues section
  refactor(pricing): extract plan card into separate component

A pre-commit hook rejects commits that don't match this pattern.
This matters because the CHANGELOG generator in Phase 11 parses commits by type.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ANTI-PATTERNS TO REJECT (FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md Section 28)
# If you (the AI) produce any of these, I will push back.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

| Anti-pattern                             | Problem                               | Correct                              |
| ---------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| <div onClick>                            | Not keyboard accessible               | <button onClick>                     |
| <div className="flex"> for nav            | Not a landmark                        | <nav>                                |
| <img src alt="..." /> no dimensions      | Causes CLS                            | Add width + height                   |
| p-[13px], text-[17px]                    | Breaks token system                   | Round to token scale                 |
| focus:outline-none with no ring          | Removes a11y focus indicator          | focus-visible:ring-2                 |
| text-xs/sm for body on mobile            | Triggers iOS zoom on inputs           | text-base minimum                    |
| w-[500px] on mobile                      | Breaks small screens                  | w-full max-w-lg                      |
| <a onClick> with no href                 | Not a link, not keyboard navigable    | <button> or add href                 |
| color: #666 hardcoded                    | Not tokenized, may fail contrast      | Use token (text-neutral-600)         |
| Hover-only tooltip with critical info    | Unreachable on touch                  | Must have tap equivalent             |
| Spinner with no label change             | Silent for screen readers             | Update text + aria-busy              |
| 100vh on mobile                          | iOS address bar overflow              | 100dvh                               |
| `any` type                               | Defeats TypeScript                    | Explicit type or `unknown`           |
| Two icon libraries                       | Visual inconsistency                  | One library (lucide-react)           |
| 3+ font families                         | Chaotic                               | Max two                              |
| Placeholder as only label                | Breaks a11y                           | Visible <label> always               |
| Inline hex colours                       | Not tokenized                         | Colour token class                   |
| Styling buttons/cards inline with utilities | Bypasses variants.ts; UI drifts       | Use buttonVariants / cardVariants    |
| Required prop with obvious default       | Friction for consumers                | Give it a default                    |
| z-[9999]                                 | Z-index collision waiting to happen   | Use token (z-modal, z-toast)         |
| Rendering nothing while loading          | Feels broken                          | Always skeleton                      |
| Error message "Error" / "Invalid input"  | Unhelpful                             | Specific, actionable message         |
| CSS shadows on dark mode                 | Invisible on dark backgrounds         | Use subtle borders instead           |
| <div role="button" tabIndex={0}>          | Reinventing <button> poorly           | Just use <button>                    |
| Numbered list where <ol> would do        | Loses semantics                       | <ol><li>...                          |
| Cramming 10 props into one component     | God-component                         | Composition (Card, CardHeader, etc.) |
| Using margin instead of gap for spacing  | Fragile                               | Parent flex/grid + gap-4             |
| padding-top + padding-bottom separately  | Verbose                               | py-*                                 |
| text-white text-[12px]                   | Arbitrary px                          | text-white text-xs                   |
| console.log in api/*                 | Not structured                        | Use src/lib/logger.ts                |
| Parsing JSON body in /api/webhook        | Breaks Stripe signature verification  | Raw body required                    |
| Creating API routes under src/api/       | Won't deploy as Vercel functions      | /api/*.ts at REPO ROOT               |
| useEffect + useState for data fetching   | Races, stale data, no retries/cache   | TanStack Query useQuery / useMutation|
| Running SQL directly in Supabase Editor  | Not versioned, not reproducible       | supabase migration new + db push     |
| Importing from siteConfig (single file)  | Type errors, broken imports           | Use site.ts / content.ts / pricing.ts |
| profiles.user_id + profiles.id           | Duplication, drift, confusion         | Single id column REFERENCES auth.users|
| Hardcoded STRIPE_PRICE_ID (monthly only) | Blocks annual billing                 | Separate MONTHLY + ANNUAL env vars   |

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REFERENCE FILES IN THIS REPO (read at session start)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md  — full frontend rules (30 sections)
- PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md   — complete folder structure and editing guide
- CLAUDE.md              — project memory, architecture decisions, known issues
- docs/brief.md          — product scope, success metrics, "not building" list
- docs/design-tokens.md  — design token decisions and rationale

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AT THE START OF EVERY SESSION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Read FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md, PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md, and CLAUDE.md before writing any code.
2. If a task is ambiguous, ask ONE clarifying question before starting.
3. Produce a plan before writing code for anything non-trivial. Wait for approval.
4. After completing a task, update CLAUDE.md with any new lessons learned.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WORK MODES (from FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md top section)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

**Mode 1 — Build mode.** Starting a new page or component:
  Read standards once at session start, then produce conformant code.
  No post-hoc checklist pass needed.

**Mode 2 — Audit mode.** Reviewing existing code:
  Walk every relevant section.
  Report PASS / FAIL / PARTIAL / N/A with file:line.
  Produce exact code fixes for every FAIL.

**Mode 3 — Single-section mode.** Working on one area (forms, dark mode, responsive):
  Load only the relevant FS section.
  Enforce it precisely without wandering into unrelated areas.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHEN YOU SHOULD PUSH BACK ON ME
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
If I ask you to:
- Use an arbitrary Tailwind value — remind me of rule 2
- Hardcode copy in a component — remind me of rule 1
- Style a button or card inline instead of using variants.ts — remind me of rule 2b
- Skip an interactive state — remind me of rule 3
- Use `any` — remind me of rule 8
- Ship without Stripe signature verification — remind me of rule 9
- Parse JSON body in the Stripe webhook — HARD STOP, breaks signature verification
- Commit an API key — HARD STOP, do not proceed
- Create a Supabase table without RLS — HARD STOP, do not proceed
- Create an API file under src/api/ — HARD STOP, it won't deploy on Vercel; use /api/ at repo root
- Deploy AI route without vercel.json maxDuration — HARD STOP, will 504 in production
- Skip maskAllInputs on PostHog session replay — HARD STOP, GDPR risk
- Fetch data via useEffect + useState when TanStack Query is the right tool — remind me of rule 12
- Modify the schema through the Supabase SQL Editor instead of a migration file — remind me to use supabase migration
- Deploy without all 7 pre-launch gates passing — remind me of the gate checklist
- Upgrade a major dependency version mid-build — remind me this is a freeze period

Your job is not to obey blindly. Your job is to protect the quality and security bar of this project.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OUTPUT DISCIPLINE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Explain changes concisely. Don't dump large code blocks without context.
- Show file:line for every change.
- For any non-trivial component, append a one-paragraph summary covering: responsive behaviour at 375/768/1280, accessibility decisions made, loading/error/empty states handled.
- Never produce TODO comments or placeholder code. Complete the implementation.
- If you can't complete something without more info, ask ONE question.

# END OF .cursorrules
